I have also had good luck with Midwest Micro.  I have a 486DX33 on my desk
and one at home that I got from them nearly 3 years ago that I use on a daily
basis and I haven't had any problems with either of them other than a drive
controller that went bad on my home machine.  Midwest Micro had a new drive
controller at my house less than 36 hours after I called them with this
problem.  It is true that they are a little difficult to get ahold of, but
it's absolutely heaven compared to trying to get anything out of Gateway or
god-forbid Dell.
